annotationA: CG4825, isoform A; CDP-diacylglycerol-serine O-phosphatidyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: phosphatidylserine biosynthetic process; neurogenesis
annotationB: Phosphatidylserine decarboxylase proenzyme, mitochondrial; Catalyzes the formation of phosphatidylethanolamine (PtdEtn) from phosphatidylserine (PtdSer). Plays a central role in phospholipid metabolism and in the interorganelle trafficking of phosphatidylserine; Belongs to the phosphatidylserine decarboxylase family. PSD-B subfamily. Eukaryotic type I sub-subfamily
